## Implementation Plan

### Phase 1: Core Timeline Engine
1. Implement timeline data structure (tracks, clips, cues)
2. Create playback engine with time management
3. Add cue list management (add, remove, reorder)
4. Implement basic playback controls (play, pause, stop)

### Phase 2: Cue System
1. Define cue structure (name, start time, duration, actions)
2. Implement cue triggering and execution
3. Add cue transitions (crossfade, cut, wipe)
4. Create cue automation (follow actions, loops)

### Phase 3: Multi-Track Support
1. Create track system (lighting, video, audio, effects)
2. Implement track-specific playback
3. Add track muting/soloing
4. Create track grouping and busing

### Phase 4: Timecode Integration
1. Implement LTC (Linear Timecode) decoder
2. Implement MTC (MIDI Timecode) receiver
3. Add NTP (Network Time Protocol) sync
4. Create timecode generator for output

### Phase 5: Show Management
1. Implement show file format (JSON/YAML)
2. Add save/load functionality
3. Create show templates and presets
4. Implement show versioning and backup

### Phase 6: UI & Control
1. Create show control UI (cue list, transport controls)
2. Add keyboard shortcuts and MIDI control
3. Implement remote control via WebSocket
4. Create monitoring dashboard

### Phase 7: Testing & Validation
1. Unit tests for timeline engine
2. Integration tests with real shows
3. Timecode sync accuracy tests
4. Performance benchmarks (FPS, latency)

